Oil Companies in South Africa to Resume Wage Talks in Effort to End Strike

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-07-15T06:31:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/south-african-oil-industry-to-restart-wage-talks-to-end-strike.html
Oil companies  operating in  South
Africa  will meet with labor unions today in an attempt to end a
wage strike that started July 11, causing motor-fuel shortages.  The talks will take place under the auspices of the
national bargaining council for the  chemical industry  and are
scheduled for July 15, 17 and 18, Clement Chitja, head of
negotiations at the Chemical, Energy, Paper, Printing, Wood and
Allied Workers Union, said by mobile phone from  Pretoria  today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carli Lourens at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net  